1175":"about 1175","1224":"1224","1145":"1145","1122":"1122","8 Aug 1145":"8 August 1145","1166":"1166","after 1140":"after 1140","Aalst,,Oost-Vlaanderen,Be":"Aalst, East Flanders, Belgium","Belgium":"Belgium","Liedekerke, Brabant Flamand, Belgique":"Liedekerke, Flemish Brabant, Belgium","Eguisheim, Haut-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Eguisheim, Haut-Rhin, Alsace, France","Forêt-sur-Vesdre, Liège, Belgique":"Forêt, Liège, Belgium","nameMeanings":[{"name":"van","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Anh, Thanh, Hung, Minh, Vinh, Dung, Hue, Huong, Lan, Quang, Tan, Thuy, Hong, Chi, Hang, Ho, Pok, Sang, Bai, Chin, Ching, Chu, Chuan, Dong.","Vietnamese (<b>Vạn</b>): from the Chinese surname 萬, see   Wan   1.","Vietnamese (<b>Văn</b>): from the Chinese surnames 文 or 聞, see   Wen   2 and 3, and also 5 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Wan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Hong, Yi, Qi, Qiang, Wai, Yiu, Yuk, Chien-Min, Fang, Hin, Jichun, Li, Man, Chung, Min, Yiping, Pak, Sik, Sung Man.  Vietnamese Tin, Bang, Da, Hien, Hoi, Lan, Minh Quang, Sau, Tich, Tung, Yaping, Yuet.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 萬, which means ‘ten thousand’ literally or ‘very great number’ figuratively: (i) from the personal name of Bi Wan (畢萬), an official in the state of Jin (located in present-day Shanxi province). He was said to be a descendant of Bi Gong Gao (known as Duke of Bi), the 15th son of the virtuous King Wen of Zhou (reined 1152–1056  BC ). Bi Wan was later granted the fiefdom of Wei (魏), which in 403  BC  became the state of Wei (located in present-day Shanxi, Shaanxi, Henan and Hebei provinces). Some of his descendants adopted Wei (魏) as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his personal name, as their surname. (ii) from the personal name Wan (萬), style name of Rui Bo (芮伯, the Earl of Rui), an official of the Western Zhou dynasty (1046–771  BC ), who was granted the fief Rui (located in Ruicheng in Shaanxi province). Some of his descendants inherited Rui (芮), the name of the fief, as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his style name, as their surname. (iii) from the placename Wan (萬), the name of a fief (located in Juxian in Shandong province) granted during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ) to an official in the ancient state of Chu. (iv) from the first element of the name of the Wan Si (萬俟) family, who lived in the downstream areas of the Yellow River during the Northern Qi dynasty (550–577  AD ). (v) from the second element of the name of the Tu Wan (吐萬) family, who are members of the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 完, meaning ‘complete’ in Chinese: (i) said to be borne by the descendants of Huan Zhui, a grandson of the Duke Huan of Song (ruler of the state of Song, died 651  BC ). (ii) from Wan (完), the name of Qu Wan (屈完), an official in the state of Chu during the Spring and Autumn Period (770–476  BC ). (iii) shortened form of the compound surname Wan-Yan (完顔), a surname from minority ethnic groups such as Juchen ethnic group in ancient northern China."]}]},{"name":"Lauretta","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["diminutive form of   Laura  , also sometimes used in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[{"name":"Loretta","meanings":["Variant of   Lauretta  , normally borne by Roman Catholics, among whom it is associated with   Loreto ."]},{"name":"Lorretta","meanings":["diminutive form of   Laura  , also sometimes used in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Lorette","meanings":["diminutive form of   Laura  , also sometimes used in the English-speaking world."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lauretta van Vlaanderen was born in 1122, in Eguisheim, Haut-Rhin, Alsace, France as the daughter of Diederik III van der Elzas and Swanhilde. She married Iwan van Aelst, Graaf van Aalst before 22 September 1139. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1175, in Forêt, Liège, Belgium, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1122–1175":"1122–1175","1090–1145":"1090–1145","1140–1224":"1140–1224","1140–1166":"1140–1166","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1090":"1090","environ 1140":"umbes 1140","1175":"1175","before 22 September 1139":"enne 22. septembrit 1139","1140":"1140","20 April 1166":"20. aprill 1166","circa 1175":"umbes 1175","1224":"1224","1145":"1145","1122":"1122","8 Aug 1145":"8. august 1145","1166":"1166","after 1140":"pärast 1140","Aalst,,Oost-Vlaanderen,Be":"Aalst, Oost-Vlaanderen, Belgia","Belgium":"Belgia","Liedekerke, Brabant Flamand, Belgique":"Liedekerke, Vlaams-Brabant, Belgia","Eguisheim, Haut-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Eguisheim, Haut-Rhin, Alsace, Prantsusmaa","Forêt-sur-Vesdre, Liège, Belgique":"Forêt, Liège, Belgia"},"fi":{"1122–1175":"1122–1175","1090–1145":"1090–1145","1140–1224":"1140–1224","1140–1166":"1140–1166","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1090":"1090","environ 1140":"noin 1140","1175":"1175","before 22 September 1139":"ennen vuotta 22. syyskuuta 1139","1140":"1140","20 April 1166":"20. huhtikuuta 1166","circa 1175":"noin 1175","1224":"1224","1145":"1145","1122":"1122","8 Aug 1145":"8. elokuuta 1145","1166":"1166","after 1140":"1140 jälkeen","Aalst,,Oost-Vlaanderen,Be":"Aalst, Oost-Vlaanderen, Belgia","Belgium":"Belgia","Liedekerke, Brabant Flamand, Belgique":"Liedekerke, Vlaams-Brabant, Belgia","Eguisheim, Haut-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Eguisheim, Haut-Rhin, Alsace, Ranska","Forêt-sur-Vesdre, Liège, Belgique":"Forêt, Liège, Belgia"},"fr":{"1122–1175":"1122–1175","1090–1145":"1090–1145","1140–1224":"1140–1224","1140–1166":"1140–1166","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1090":"1090","environ 1140":"environ 1140","1175":"1175","before 22 September 1139":"avant 22 septembre 1139","1140":"1140","20 April 1166":"20 avril 1166","circa 1175":"environ 1175","1224":"1224","1145":"1145","1122"